# DocumentDB Gateway Configuration
#
# This file is loaded by the documentdb-gateway systemd unit via
# EnvironmentFile=. Edit this file to configure the gateway, then
# restart the service:
#
#   sudo systemctl restart documentdb-gateway
#
# IMPORTANT: This release only supports LOCAL PostgreSQL with peer/trust
# authentication over a Unix socket. Cloud-managed PostgreSQL (AWS RDS,
# Azure Database for PostgreSQL, Aiven, etc.) over TCP with password
# authentication is NOT supported in this release. See Track 2 in the
# packaging design document for the planned remote-PG support.
#
# ─── PostgreSQL connection (required) ───────────────────────────────
#
# Path to a file containing the PostgreSQL connection URL.
# The gateway reads the URL from the file at startup. The file must
# be readable by the documentdb-gateway OS user (typically mode 0640,
# owner root:documentdb-gateway).
#
# For stand-alone installs (documentdb-N), documentdb-register-gateway /
# documentdb-setup writes this file at the per-major persistent path
# below. The path is under /var/lib/ (not /run/) so it survives reboot;
# a tmpfs /run-based path would dangle on next boot because this env
# file persists but the URL file would be cleared by tmpfs. See
# packaging-design.md §4.3 for the rationale.
#
# DOCUMENTDB_PG_URL_FILE=/var/lib/documentdb-local/N/gateway/pg-url
#
# ─── Listen address ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Address and port the gateway binds to. Default: :10260
#
# DOCUMENTDB_LISTEN_ADDR=:10260
#
# ─── TLS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Paths to the TLS certificate and private key. When both are set
# the gateway uses them instead of auto-generating a self-signed
# certificate.
#
# DOCUMENTDB_TLS_CERT_FILE=
# DOCUMENTDB_TLS_KEY_FILE=
#
# Auto-generate a self-signed certificate if no cert/key files are
# provided. Default: true.
#
# DOCUMENTDB_TLS_AUTO_GENERATE=true
#
# Directory where DOCUMENTDB_TLS_AUTO_GENERATE=true writes (and reuses
# on restart) the self-signed cert.pem / pkey.pem pair. Default:
# /var/lib/documentdb-gateway/tls. Use this when the gateway runs with
# a non-default WorkingDirectory or when you want certs in a backup-
# friendly location.
#
# DOCUMENTDB_TLS_STATE_DIR=/var/lib/documentdb-gateway/tls
#
# ─── Logging ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# DOCUMENTDB_LOG_LEVEL=info
